<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-BLITZ-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS' ANTI-BLITZ MEASURES WILL GET ULTIMATE TEST
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RAY BUCK 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Dallas Cowboys running backs collectively have
missed picking up only one blitz in two seasons, a handy strength
to have, especially this week against blitz-happy Philadelphia at
Veterans Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   ``They do it all,'' Cowboys running backs coach Clarence Shelmon
said of the Eagles' defense. ``They'll send as many as nine at a
time.''
</P>
<P>
   So whether it's Emmitt Smith/Tim Lester in the two-back set, or
either Smith or third-down back Chris Warren in the one-back set,
Dallas will need a letter-perfect game Sunday from its running
backs on blitz pickup if they hope to keep quarterback Troy Aikman
on his feet in Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
   ``Emmitt is every bit as good at picking up the blitz as he is
at running the football,'' Shelmon said. ``He's one of the best at
blitz pickup that I've ever seen. He has really good leverage, and
he delivers a good pop.''
</P>
<P>
   Philadelphia will blitz as much as 45-50 percent of the time,
based on what the Cowboys have seen on videotape of Philly's first
four games under first-year defensive coordinator Jim Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   The Eagles are 0-4, but they have recorded six sacks and 32
quarterback hurries to go along with their NFL-leading 12
takeaways. Blitzing is a gamble that apparently the winless Birds
aren't afraid to take.
</P>
<P>
   Speedy middle linebacker Jeremiah Trotter and left cornerback
Troy Vincent have one sack apiece. Free safety Brian Dawkins has
three QB hurries. Nickel backer Ike Reese has one sack and two
hurries.
</P>
<P>
   Philadelphia especially likes to use the zone blitz. The Eagles
will send a safety and linebacker, or they will send both the
cornerback and outside linebacker from the same side to rush the
passer, leaving the outside receiver on that side uncovered coming
off the line of scrimmage.
</P>
<P>
   Aside from picking up the overload, the Cowboys will need for
their receivers to properly read blitz and for Aikman to quickly
deliver the ball. Short drops will be employed. This, of course,
can result in some big plays, especially with Raghib ``Rocket''
Ismail's speed added to the lineup this season.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys allowed no sacks last week against Arizona. Aikman
was neither rushed nor even touched by Arizona's defense.
</P>
<P>
   ``We did a great job of picking up the blitz,'' coach Chan
Gailey said. ``In fact, we did a better job of picking up the blitz
than we did with our base stuff.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
