<P>
   BBA-REDSOX (Boston) -- After a decade of divas _ the
high-maintenance soap operas involving tempestuous types like Roger
Clemens and Mo Vaughn _ Sox fans were ready to embrace a group of
players not embarrassed to have a little dirt under their
fingernails. By Gordon Edes. 1560 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX-SHAUGHNESSY-COLUMN (Boston) -- Otherwise rational
people suddenly think the Sox are going to win the World Series for
the first time since 1918. By Dan Shaughnessy. 860 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX-WILLIAMS (Boston) -- For the second year in a row,
Jimy Williams is receiving accolades for somehow getting the Red
sox to Cleveland as the American League wild card. By Bob Duffy.
1800 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX-MARTINEZ (Boston) -- Pedro Martinez is on a truly
incredible roll. In his last seven starts, he went 6-0 with an 0.82
ERA, including 96 strikeouts and only 28 hits in 55 innings. By Dan
Shaughnessy. 1300 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX-VARITEK (Cleveland) -- Jason Varitek refuses to
undervalue himself. Jason Varitek refuses to overvalue himself. By
Bob Duffy. 1380 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX-DUQUETTE (Cleveland) -- With the Red Sox advancing to
the playoffs for the third time in five full seasons under his
watch, Dan Duquette has become less a lightning rod and more of a
beacon of hope for fans. By Gordon Edes. 1900 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-INDIANS (Cleveland) -- The numbers on the stat sheet appear
to be part of someone's creative writing project. They are not
really the Cleveland Indians, they are Jacobs Field's Men of
Fiction. By Michael Holley. 875 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-INDIANS-HARGROVE (Cleveland) -- Mike Hargrove is fresh off
his fifth consecutive division title, primed to step over the Red
Sox on the way to his third World Series. By Bob Duffy. 1280 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-CLEVELAND-RAMIREZ (Cleveland) -- Manny Ramirez is almost
reverential in his regard for his supporting cast, a term he would
never use to describe them. By Bob Duffy. 1345 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-CLEVELAND-COLON (Cleveland) -- Bartolo Colon idolizes his
fellow Dominican native, Pedro Martinez, but the homage is getting
ridiculous. By Bob Duffy. 400 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-CAMERAS (Cleveland) -- The notorious I Spy camera in center
field will remain covered in white canvas, as it has been for two
weeks, per the American League at the behest of the Sox. By Bob
Duffy. 575 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
