   PREGAME PRAYER-TEXAS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   STEPHENVILLE, Texas _ At many rural Texas high schools, a prayer
before a weekend football game has been as much a part of the
autumn ritual as exuberant cheerleaders, die-hard boosters and
homecoming queens. But a recent ruling by the 5th U.S. Circuit
Court of Appeals silences school-sponsored prayer at the games. The
court action, some local officials and pastors say, runs contrary
to the deeply held religious beliefs shared by many people in these
Bible-belt communities. Some schools openly defy the ruling, others
use imaginative maneuvers to get around it, and all bemoan the
interference of government in their Friday night rites. By BARRY
SHLACHTER. Story has moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
