<P>
   BELLSOUTH _ In the wake of the failed bid for Sprint, BellSouth
CEO Duane Ackerman sends a letter (via email) to his 80,000-plus
employees trying to explain what happened. The AJC has a copy.
(Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Consitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNETCONF _ Overview of the buzz at Internet World _ what are
these companies trying to sell as the future of Internet
technologies? Most likely, it'll be different ways of making us
more dependent on the Internet, like with net appliances and
internet phones. Also prolly some comments from the two keynotes,
Craig Barrett and Larry Ellison. (Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   CINNABON _ AFC's Cinnabon announced a deal to open more than a
dozen units in Puerto Rico. (Poole, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DELL _ For most of this year, Dell Computer Corp. has expanded
its reach into different customer groups with new products and
Internet services. It has consistently outperformed the PC industry
and its top competitors. With their usual confidence, senior
executives have told Wall Street about plans that would double
revenue to about $40 billion in the next several years. So why has
the stock, which typically set new highs several times a year, been
unable to get near its all- time high of $55 set last February?
(Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   COKE-SUIT _ Plaintiffs in the racial discrimination case against
Coca-Cola today are expected to file a brief related to allegations
of document shredding by the company. (Unger, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
