   CARE _ ATLANTA _ CARE, abandoning its longtime policy of being
strictly non-political, is engaged in a full-court lobbying press
for a political solution in to the civil war in Sudan. (Melvin,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   CLINT0N-TREATY _ WASHINGTON _ Using the bully pulpit to try to
salvage a key foreign policy initiative, President Clinton appealed
to the American people Wednesday to get behind a nuclear test ban
treaty that appeared headed for defeat in a Senate sharply split
along partisan lines. (Deans, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   ANTS _ WASHINGTON _ Some of the isolationist views of Republican
presidential candidate Pat Buchanan appeared to be shared by a
group of ants that live in acacia trees in Africa. For years,
entomologists have puzzled over the ants' strange behavior of
pruning the trees they occupy, even to the detriment of the trees.
Now, in a paper published in this week's Nature, biologists say
they prune the trees to separate them from surrounding trees, which
are occupied by several different, fiercer species of ants.
(Nesmith, Cox News Service). 15.
</P>
<P>
   TUTU _ WASHINGTON _ Archbishop Desmond Tutu, chairman of the
Truth and Reconciliation Commission in South Africa, addresses a
National Press Club luncheon. (Hill, Cox News Service). 15.
</P>
<P>
   CHEM-BIO _ WASHINGTON _ Military and civilian authorities are
responding to the threat of chemical and biological terrorism with
Cold War approaches that are doomed to failure, an expert on
unconventional threats told a conference of government officials
and technology companies this week. The two-day meeting, sponsored
by Jane's Information Group, the London-based publisher of
information on weapons systems, ends Wednesday. It is being
attended by representatives of the Secret Service, the Central
Intelligence Agency, various military agencies and a few local
officials, including Austin, Texas, police detective Jim Neilson
and fire department hazmat chief David Fiero. Neilson says Austin
is somewhat unique in the cooperative preparation fire and police
departments are attempting to make to chem-bio dangers. (Nesmith,
Cox News Service). 25.
</P>
<P>
   MANAGEDCARE _ WASHINGTON _ Developments in the debate on
competing managed care bills. (Carr, Cox News Service).
</P>
