<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on . . .
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Mike Newell
</P>
<P>
   (director, ``Pushing Tin'')
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Donnie Brasco'' (1997, R). Johnny Depp plays a cop who
infiltrates the mob through father figure Al Pacino.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Four Weddings and a Funeral'' (1994, R). Hugh Grant
fumbles, stumbles and finally expresses his feelings to Andie
MacDowell in this romantic comedy.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Enchanted April'' (1991, PG ). Joan Plowright, Miranda
Richardson and Polly Walker let their hair down in an Italian
villa.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Good Father'' (1987, R). Anthony Hopkins meddles in the
custody battle of new friend Jim Broadbent in this compelling
psychological drama.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Dance With a Stranger'' (1985, R). Miranda Richardson
romances Rupert Everett in this melodrama based on a real murder
case.
</P>
