</P>
<P>
   FOREIGN AID FOR FAMILY PLANNING
</P>
<P>
   The United States is by far the largest supporter of population
assistance among developed countries, spending $637.7 million in
1996. But as a portion of national wealth, the U.S. foreign aid
budget is lowest, only slightly more than one-tenth of 1 percent.
</P>
