<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Oct. 7 and thereafter. For questions about stories, please contact
Susan Leh at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   BELMONT-TESTS (Los Angeles) _ The first set of confirmatory
tests of toxic gases below the Belmont Learning Center show levels
of the deadly hydrogen sulfide gas at twice as many locations and
at maximum levels ten times those detected last spring, state
toxics officials said Wednesday. By Beth Barrett. (Will move in the
``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTHY-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Bryan and Kelly Skinner of
Agoura had nine boys and _ finally! _ they were blessed with a
girl, Daisy. Although Bryan wanted 12 kids, Kelly says this is it.
She's tired. By Dennis McCarthy. (Will move in the ``a'' national
and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   HMO-SUIT (Los Angeles) _ Blue Cross of California was sued
Wednesday by two subscribers who claim the HMO secretly imposed a
20 percent surcharge on their premiums. The suit, filed in Los
Angeles Superior Court on Wednesday, seeks class-action status. By
Chris Sieroty. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
