<P>
   GORE-NORTHWEST (Seattle) _ Vice President Al Gore, once
considered to have a lock on the Democratic presidential
nomination, is facing increasing pressure in Washington state and
the West from his fast-rising challenger, former Sen. Bill Bradley.
Bradley's campaign in the Pacific Northwest is showing signs of
catching on as rapidly as in the East, where polls show the former
