<P>
   &UR; HOMEWORK  &LR; _ The big buzz word in education these days is
``accountability.'' The Internet is playing an increasing role in
fostering accountability by allowing parents to keep tabs on their
kids via online posting of homework assignments, attendance and
grades. Both private companies and school districts themselves are
offering related services. But the trend has been slow to catch on
in the San Francisco Bay Area, where wired homes and schools are
offset by a more liberal sensibility. Parents here aren't clamoring
to play Big Brother. BY DAVID LAZARUS.
</P>
