institution has curated part of an exhibition by buying artifacts
via the Internet. ``I've addicted half the museum to Ebay,'' he
says. (Angel Franco/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) AUGUSTA, Ga. -- Oct. 6, 1999 -- NORWOOD-PROFILE, 10-06 --
Rep. Charlie Norwood, R-Ga., during a hearing on health care at a
hospital in his home district. Norwood, a dentist, is pushing his
own party leaders for new managed care regulations. (Alan S.
Weiner/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) UNDATED -- Oct. 6, 1999 -- KOCH-COX-B&AMP;W, 10-06 --
Testimony is under way in the latest legal battle between William
Koch, left, of Palm Beach, and the company led by two of his
brothers - one of them his twin, David, also of Palm Beach, seen
here with his wife Julia. Although the government is the named
plaintiff in a case involving how the company, Koch Industries,
measured oil it obtained under leases from the federal government
and American Indian tribes, the Justice Department is not
participating in the case. It's being bankrolled by William Koch,
who stands to gain as much as one-third of a judgment for the
government under a whistle-blower statute. (Palm Beach Daily
News/Cox News Service Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) LONGVIEW, Texas -- Oct. 6, 1999 -- SERVICE-DOG-COX-2,
10-06 -- Matthew Coates pets his service dog Carol at home. Of the
89 commands Matthew can give Carol, to assist him in his everyday
life, one of his favorite is ``Carol, lap.'' ``I like that command.
She gets in my lap, and I can hug her or whatever,'' Matthew said.
Carol, a white golden retriever, was a special delivery to Matthew
from the Make A Wish Foundation. She is a service dog from the
Assistance Dog Institute in Rohnert Park, Calif. (Bahram Mark
Sobhani/Longview News Journal)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) LONGVIEW, Texas -- Oct. 6, 1999 -- SERVICE-DOG-COX-1,
10-06 -- Matthew Coates is taken to his next class by Elisha
Pierce, his instructional assistant, as his service dog, Carol,
walks along side. Carol, a white golden retriever, was a special
delivery to Matthew from the Make A Wish Foundation. She is a
service dog from the Assistance Dog Institute in Rohnert Park,
Calif. The pouch on her back carries some of Matthew's school
supplies. (Bahram Mark Sobhani/Longview News Journal)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
